<br>
You mean tracking experience, correct?<br>
<br>
It's done using the Command Chat Channel feature. To set this up you:<br>
1) Create a chat channel in EQ or EQ-II<br>
2) Assign this chat channel to be your Command Chat Channel in EQC's preferences (I believe the channel name is case sensitive)<br>
3) Send commands to this channel using syntax like &quot;/1 say Hello!&quot; where the /1 is your chat channel number.<br>
<br>
The command for experience tracking is simply &quot;/1 EXP 50&quot; for example. If you are tracking AA-experience (EQ1) you use &quot;/1 AA 50&quot;. These commands would tell that you are currently at 50% into your level / AA level.<br>
<br>
The first time you do this, EQC sets your initial experience level. Each consecutive EXP or AA command will calculate how much experience you have gained since the initial value and speak out loud how much experience per hour you have gained.<br>
<br>
You can enter your experience as a decimal number (like 28.1 for 28.1%). As far as I know there is no good way in EQ1 to figure out the percentage with this precision but in EQ-II you can use some customized UI components which will tell your current experience level to this precision.<br>
<br>
By the way, if you are using EQC in on-line parsing, you can send command '/1 help' and the text window will show all the commands available. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p067.ezboard.com/beqcompanion.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eqcompanion>EQ Companion</A> at: 7/15/05 11:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p067.ezboard.com/beqcompanion.showUserPublicProfile?gid=auldian>Auldian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#330000>(7/15/05 1:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=409.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Training &quot;experience&quot; is done how?</span><hr size=1> Excellent thank you. I didn't realize it had the &quot;help&quot; feature. I'll take a look at that too when I get back in game. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Broogan Dreadbow</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=977800"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>What's so funny...?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=409.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=409.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=409.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td